Here is the Julia code implementing your requirement:

```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump=3)
    return dt + Dates.Hour(bump)
end

function timezone_bumper(d::Date)
    throw(ArgumentError("Only DateTime type is allowed but got $d"))
end
```
This function `timezone_bumper` takes a DateTime and an optional bump argument, which defaults to 3. It then returns the original DateTime plus the bump hours. If you try to use it with a Date, it will throw an error.
